  "prompt": "Upto which rank does a reserved category student get IRS (IT)?",
  "response": "The rank required for a reserved category student to get into Indian Revenue Service (Income Tax), commonly known as IRS (IT), can vary each year based on the results of the Civil Services Examination conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC). Generally, a reserved category student (belonging to SC, ST, or OBC categories) might secure IRS (IT) with a rank approximately ranging from 350 to 700, depending on the yearly vacancy, cut-off marks, and their respective category reservations. Candidates should always refer to the latest UPSC results and cut-offs for the most accurate and updated information.",
